results.name: Number of partitions of n into distinct composite parts.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller and Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000 (terms n = 0..250 from Reinhard Zumkeller)
formula: G.f.: (1/(1 + x))*Product_{k>=1} (1 + x^k)/(1 + x^prime(k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Dec 31 2016
maple: b(n, i-1)+ `if`(i>n or isprime(i), 0, b(n-i, i-1))))
mathematica: b[n_, i_] := b[n, i] = If[n==0, 1, If[i<2, 0, b[n, i-1] + If[i>n || PrimeQ[i], 0, b[n-i, i-1]]]]; a[n_] := b[n, n]; Table[a[n], {n, 0, 70}] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Oct 22 2015, after _Alois P. Heinz_ *)
program: p (k:ks) m = if m < k then 0 else p ks (m - k) + p ks m
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 15 2012
